description: The Open Graph protocol enables any web page to become a rich object in a social graph. For instance, this is used on Facebook to allow any web page to have the same functionality as any other object on Facebook.
label: The Open Graph protocol

audio:album.description: [DEPRECATED] An album to which some audio belongs.
audio:album.label: audio album

audio:secure_url.description: A relevant, secure audio URL for your object.
audio:secure_url.label: audio secure URL

audio:type.description: The mime type of an audio file e.g., "application/mp3"
audio:type.label: audio type

audio.description: A relevant audio URL for your object.
audio.label: audio

country-name.description: [DEPRECATED] The country name of the resource e.g., "USA"
country-name.label: country name

description.description: A one to two sentence description of your object.
description.label: description

determiner.description: The word to precede the object's title in a sentence (e.g., "the" in "the statue of liberty").  Valid values are "a", "an", "the", "", and "auto".
determiner.label: determiner

email.description: [DEPRECATED] Email of the contact for your object.
email.label: email

fax_number.description: [DEPRECATED] Fax number of the contact for your object.
fax_number.label: fax number

image:secure_url.description: A secure image URL which should represent your object within the graph.
image:secure_url.label: image secure url

image:type.description: The mime type of an image.
image:type.label: image type

image.description: An image URL which should represent your object within the graph.
image.label: image

isbn.description: [DEPRECATED] International Standard Book Number for you object.
isbn.label: International Standard Book Number

latitude.description: [DEPRECATED] The latitude of the resource e.g., the latitude of a company.
latitude.label: latitude

locale.description: A Unix locale in which this markup is rendered.
locale.label: locale

locality.description: [DEPRECATED] The locality of the resource e.g, "Palo Alto"
locality.label: locality

longitude.description: [DEPRECATED] The longitude of the resource e.g., the longitude of a company.
longitude.label: longitude

phone_number.description: [DEPRECATED] Phone number of the contact for your object.
phone_number.label: phone number

postal-code.description: [DEPRECATED] The postal code of the resource e.g., "94304"
postal-code.label: postal code

region.description: [DEPRECATED] The region of the resource e.g., "CA"
region.label: region

site_name.description: If your object is part of a larger web site, the name which should be displayed for the overall site. e.g., "IMDb".
site_name.label: site name

street-address.description: [DEPRECATED] The street address of the resource e.g., "1601 S California Ave".
street-address.label: street address

title.description: The title of the object as it should appear within the graph, e.g.,  "The Rock".
title.label: title

type.description: The type of your object, e.g., "movie".  Depending on the type you specify, other properties may also be required.
type.label: type

upc.description: [DEPRECATED] Universal Product Code for your object.
upc.label: universal product code

url.description: The canonical URL of your object that will be used as its permanent ID in the graph, e.g., "http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0117500/".
url.label: url

video:secure_url.description: A relevant, secure video URL for your object.
video:secure_url.label: video secure URL

video:type.description: The mime type of a video e.g., "application/x-shockwave-flash"
video:type.label: video type

video.description: A relevant video URL for your object.
video.label: video
